MCP Client for Ollama for Debian

MCP Client for Ollama (ollmcp) is a modern, interactive terminal application 
for connecting local Ollama LLMs to Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers.

Requirements:
 - Python 3.10 or newer
 - Ollama running locally (https://ollama.com/download)

Usage:
 Start the client by running:
   mcp-client-for-ollama

 Or using the alias:
   ollmcp

Configuration:
 MCP server configurations are typically stored in:
 - ~/.config/Claude/mcp.json (auto-discovered for Claude setups)
 - Custom paths can be configured through the application

For more information, see the upstream documentation at:
https://github.com/jonigl/mcp-client-for-ollama

